{"_id":"fgnxFVO5M1sCIXHw","name":"Brittle","content":"<p>When struck with a weapon featuring the Kinetic rule (e.g. arquebus, hammer, mace, etc.), the actor takes extra damage as if the weapon's base damage was 2 higher. For example, a mace ordinarily inflicts Damage + 2, but inflicts Damage + 4 versus a target afflicted with brittle status.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"poY8veEe74BAZKzN","name":"Burning (Fire)","content":"<p>The actor takes 2 HP damage per turn, or every few seconds outside of combat, ignoring armor, until that actor both moves away from the source of the fire and spends an action extinguishing herself.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"vXBuNTlJ0SoLHibp","name":"Conductive","content":"<p>When exposed to electricity, the actor takes 2 HP damage per factor (i.e. metallic weapon, metallic armor, soaking wet, etc.) instead of 1 HP damage per factor.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EKckANntw3XFM1zK","name":"Corroding (Acid)","content":"<p>The actor takes 1 HP damage per turn, or every few seconds outside of combat, ignoring armor, until that actor spends an action removing the corroding parts of her outfit (and negates her outfit's DR until it is repaired). If the actor cannot \"shed\" the melting parts of an outfit (i.e. a creature, an actor that is not wearing an outfit that has DR, etc.), exposure to acid simply results in a mortal wound.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"CdMWiyeD1Dct2R2z","name":"Critical Wound","content":"<p>When the actor moves and acts during her turn, instead of opting to just move or act, she takes 1 HP damage, ignor\u0002ing armor. An actor has either a critical wound or a mortal wound, but not both concurrently. A second critical wound upgrades to a mortal wound.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"8LwWGQYOCt3QbphJ","name":"Flammable","content":"<p>When afflicted with burning status, the actor takes 4 HP dam\u0002age per turn instead of 2 HP damage per turn.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"1RbEWfuuBK93LTMR","name":"Leaky","content":"<p>The actor suffers 2 HP damage instead of 1 HP damage when aggravating a critical would (i.e. moving and acting during a turn) or bleeding out from a mortal wound.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"JZEjDxIYFGrHMXAf","name":"Mortal Wound","content":"<p>The actor takes 1 HP damage per turn, or every one minute outside of combat, ignoring armor. An actor has either a critical wound or a mortal wound, but not both concurrently.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"1MZVHBAP6toFK8jP","name":"Poisoned (Strong)","content":"<p>The actor suffers from a mortal wound that can only be stabilized by drinking a strong antidote (or better). An actor can be afflicted with either strong poison or weak poison, but not both.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"XBSu8s38Ka065eT5","name":"Poisoned (Weak)","content":"<p>The actor suffers from a critical wound that can only be stabilized by drinking a weak antidote (or better). An actor can be afflicted with either strong poison or weak poison, but not both.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"k5JnEQHIIsSKrqa7","name":"Slowed","content":"<p>The actor loses her movement during combat (though she can still convert her action into a movement). She regains her movement after she has \"worked through\" the impediment after having it for a number of turns (usually a number of turns equal to hits rolled against her, or some arbitrary value determined by the GM based on what's slowing her down).</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"X9z2DYJYdKVBMW3O","name":"Soaked (Water)","content":"<p>The actor is immune to burning status, but takes an additional 1 HP damage, ignoring armor, when struck with electricity. This status effect can stack with conductive status. The actor remains soaked until she changes her outfit or lets her outfit dry off over the course of a downtime session. Any black powder weapon (e.g. arquebus, blunderbuss, pistol, etc.) or bomb that was on her person when she was soaked is rendered inert until it dries off over the course of a downtime session.Â </p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"dIBdhPro6ce2Lnnr":3},"flags":{}}
